│                                                                                                                                       │
│              $$ \frac{dq}{dt} = \frac{\partial H}{\partial p} = \frac{p}{3} \Rightarrow \frac{dX}{dt} = \frac{p}{3} \Rightarrow \text│
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              Next, Hamilton’s eqn #1:                                                                                                 │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│              \frac{dq}{dt} = \frac{\partial H}{\partial p} = \frac{p}{3} \Rightarrow \frac{dX}{dt} = \frac{p}{3}                      │
│              \Rightarrow \text{Solve for p:} \quad p = 3 \cdot \dot{x}                                                                │
