│              So, ok. Everything checks out!                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              Then, for the next step:                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│              \frac{dp}{dt} = \frac{\partial H}{\partial q} = \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( \frac{p^2}{6} + x^2 \right) = 2x \qua│
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              So:                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│              \frac{dp}{dt} = -\frac{\partial H}{\partial q} = -2x \quad \text{as above.}                                              │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              Now, bring everything together.                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              So, put it all in symbolic terms:                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              Set up:                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              $$ \text{Variables: } q = x, \quad p = \text{defined as per chain rule} $$                                               │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              So, in summary:                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              ### END OF REVISION                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              📌 Final Answer Summary:                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              COORDINATES: q = x                                                                                                       │
│              MOMENTUM: p = m * dot(x) = 3 * dot(x) = 3 * dv/dt? No! Keep track:                                                       │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│              p = \frac{dp}{dt} = m \cdot \dot{q}_{total} = \text{Not important. Just leave it as is}.                                 │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              Anyway, following the path clearly shows:                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              > Final Formulas Used:                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│              \begin{aligned}                                                                                                          │
│              & \text{Energy: } T = \frac{p^2}{2m} = \frac{p^2}{2 \cdot 3} = \frac{p^2}{6} \\                                          │
│              & V = x^2 \\                                                                                                             │
│              & H = T + V = \frac{p^2}{6} + x^2 \Rightarrow H = \frac{p^2}{6} + x^2                                                    │
│              \end{aligned}                                                                                                            │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              Apply Hamilton’s equations:                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                       │
│              $$                                                                                                                       │
│              \begin{aligned}                                                                                                          │
│              \text{First equation:} && \frac{dq}{dt} = \frac{\partial H}{\partial p} = \frac{\partial}{\partial p} \                  │
