│                                                                COMPLETION                                                                │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ ### METHOD:                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ **Step 1:**                                                                                                                              │
│ Choose **generalized coordinates**: $ q = x $                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ ---                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ **Step 2:**                                                                                                                              │
│ Write **conjugated momentum** $ p $:                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│ p = \frac{dq}{dt} \cdot m \quad \text{(mass)} = \frac{\partial L}{\partial v}                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ But here we write it directly as:                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ Since the mass is given ($ m = 1 $), define:                                                                                             │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│ p = m \cdot \dot{x} = \dot{x}                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ So,                                                                                                                                      │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│ p = \dot{x}, \quad \text{and since } m = 1,\quad \boxed{p = \dot{x}}                                                                     │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ ---                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ **Step 3:**                                                                                                                              │
│ Kinetic Energy $ T $:                                                                                                                    │
│ From classical mechanics,                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│ T = \frac{p^2}{2m} = \frac{\dot{x}^2}{2(1)}                                                                                              │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ Thus,                                                                                                                                    │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│ T = \frac{1}{2}\dot{x}^2 = \frac{(\dot{x})^2}{2}                                                                                         │
│ $$                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ ---                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ **Step 4:**                                                                                                                              │
│ Potential energy $ V(q): $ Spring has stiffness $ k = 10000 $ N/m, mass $ m = 1 $. So:                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ - Kinetic term already includes $ \dot{x} $                                                                                              │
│ - Potential due to spring:                                                                                                               │
│     $$ V_{spring} = \frac{k}{2}(x)^2 = \frac{10000}{2}x^2 = 5000x^2 $$                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                          │
│ No other forces mentioned—assume no gravitational or external field acting on this simple harmonic oscillator model.                     │
