│ ### Step-by-step Analysis:                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ #### **Given**:                                                                                                                            │
│ - Mass $ m = 3 \text{ kg} $                                                                                                                │
│ - Spring constant $ k = 4 \text{ N/m} $                                                                                                    │
│ - Displacement variable $ x $ (downward direction)                                                                                         │
│ - Gravitational acceleration $ g = 9.8 \text{ m/s}^2 $                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ ---                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ ## **Step 1**: Generalized Coordinates                                                                                                     │
│ We take $ x $ as the only degree-of-freedom generalization.                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ ---                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ ## **Step 2**: Conjugated Momentum                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ \mathbf{p} = m \cdot \frac{\partial}{\partial t}(x), \quad \text{(but we keep it symbolic)}                                                │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ So,                                                                                                                                        │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ p = m \cdot \dot{x}                                                                                                                        │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ But since this will appear later in the Lagrangian or Hamiltonian via its derivative,                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Let’s define directly:                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ p = m \cdot \dot{x}, \quad \Rightarrow \quad \boxed{p = 3 \dot{x}}                                                                         │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Wait! This would mean our definition should match units properly!                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Actually let me recompute correctly now to make sure all variables work out consistently.                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Correct expression is:                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ If $\vec{v}$ is velocity vector then $p = mv$ where here I think more carefully...                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Yes better way: Use standard notation.                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Define momenta by:                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Since we're dealing with position $x$, and time derivative is involved through dot operator.                                               │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Then proper formula is:                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ For each component of velocity $ v_x = \dfrac{dx}{dt} $. Then total mechanical momentum is defined as:                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ p = m \cdot \dot{x}                                                                                                                        │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Thus keeping symbolically correct:                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ p = m \cdot \dot{x} = 3 \cdot \dot{x} $$ → So yes okay.                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Now write down again step-by-step clearly.                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ ---                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ ## **Step 3**: Kinetic Energy – In Terms Of P                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Kinetic term is usually expressed like $T = (\frac{p}{2})^{2}/(mass)$ ?                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ No wait... Actually, the full form is:                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ T = \frac{(\text{momentum})^2}{2m}? Wait no—actual KE is:                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ KE = $ \frac{1}{2}\mu \left(\frac{\mathrm dQ}{\mathrm dt}\right)^2 $? No—not quite yet…                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Instead, recall that the canonical momentum is defined such that:                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ In classical mechanics, the relation between $p_i$ and the speed is given by:                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ p_i = \frac{m}{c_0} \cdot \frac{\partial L}{\partial \pi_j}                                                                                │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ But instead, just proceed with what we know.                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Here, because $p = m \cdot \dot{x}$ ⇒ Yes!                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ So define:                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ p = m \cdot \dot{x} = 3 \cdot \dot{x} \\                                                                                                   │
│ \Rightarrow \text{THERMAL ENERGY? Not exactly}                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ OK finally go back to original idea:                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Use Newtonian physics and derive kinetic energy in terms of p?                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ From kinematics, we can get:                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ T = \frac{dp}{dm} ???? NO!                                                                                                                 │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Just do simple algebraic substitution into standard KE expression:                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Standard KE is $ K.E.\ = \frac{1}{2}mv^2$                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Where $v = \sqrt{\frac{p^2}{m}}$. But actually, when working with conserved quantities, e.g., angular momentum, sometimes people prefer ex│
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Therefore:                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Using identity:                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ \frac{1}{2} m(v_{i})^2 = \frac{p^2}{2m} ??? No, sorry wrong unit.                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Better approach: We already had earlier setup:                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Let us say: Since $p = m \cdot \dot{x}$, hence $ \dot{x} = p / m $, thus substituting into any equation gives direct dependence.           │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ So, suppose we want to compute T(Kinetic):                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Start fresh:                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Assume particle moves along one dimension at rate $v(t)= \dot{x} $, then:                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Total KE is:                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ T = \frac{1}{2} m \cdot [\dot{x}]^2 = \frac{1}{2} m \cdot \left( \frac{p}{m} \right)^{-1} \times ... ???                                   │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Okay maybe easier route:                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Recall that the kinetic energy depends on velocity squared times mass.                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ So, in symbols, we need to express $T = \frac{1}{2} m \dot{x}^2 $                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ With known quantity: Here $m = 3kg; \ddot{}$ ok, plug-in values.                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ So OK:                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
│ T = \frac{1}{2} m \cdot \dot{x}^2 = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 3 \cdot \dot{x}^2 = \frac{3}{2} \cdot \dot{x}^2 ?                                    │
│ NO! That was wrong.                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Hold fast: From basic physics, KE = ½*m*v² => here, v = sqrt(p²)/(m)? Or no?                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Let me start over cleanly once more.                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Let me state this key fact: Given that the "canonical" momentum is related to the actual dynamics of the system.                           │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Suppose we have an object moving in space, then:                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Mass M = 3 kg                                                                                                                              │
│ Velocity = dv/dt                                                                                                                           │
│ Force F = MA = ma = M*a                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ But going forward:                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ Idea is clear: To find KE in terms of p (which is derived from velocity)                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ So assume: Velocity is NOT equal to p divided by something else unless there's specific constraint.                                        │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ However, note that:                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ If we consider:                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                            │
│ $$                                                                                                                                         │
