│                                                                                                                                           │
│    (because k = 6 N/m, so half-k multiplied by x squared yields 3x²)                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                           │
│ 2. **Gravitational:** Consider the effect of gravity. Mass M = 3 kg, g = 9.8 m/s², acting downward.                                       │
│                                                                                                                                           │
│    Let’s define the potential energy due to gravity. If x is downward-directed (and assumed to be positive downward), then the gravitatio│
